T1  - An ex-ante model for estimating the impact on trade flows of a country's joining a customs union
AU  - Corado, Cristina
AU  - De Melo, Jaime
JO  - Journal of Development Economics
VL  - 24
IS  - 1
SP  - 153
EP  - 166
PY  - 1986
DA  - 1986/11/01/
SN  - 0304-3878
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3878(86)90151-3
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304387886901513
AB  - This paper presents a structural ex-ante model to estimate the extent of trade creation and trade diversion associated with a country's joining a customs union. The model extends previous studies by explicitly introducing exports and product differentiation to the determination of trade creation and trade diversion. Unlike the traditional Vinerian analysis, where the role of exports is neglected, the model handles the effects of eliminating the common external tariff facing home exports. The model is then applied to Portugal's joining the European Community. Estimates of trade diversion are presented at a disaggregated level along with likely welfare effects of Portugal's joining the Community.
ER  - 

