DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3878(86)90143-4
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304387886901434
AB  - This essay is concerned with the extent to which expectations of depreciation and the degree of uncertainty with respect to the future exchange rate policy may modify the pricing behavior of the domestic firm. It turns out that the optimal price under uncertainty will be larger than in the certain case, if the ‘price loss’, due to under-estimation of demand, is larger than the marginal cost of holding inventories. The model was tested with data for Argentina for the period before the collapse of the exchange rate system in March 1981.
ER  - 

